8 .  What is a Variable (in Terraform)?
A variable in Terraform is a placeholder used to store a value so you don’t have to hard‑code information in your infrastructure code.
👉 Variables make Terraform code reusable, flexible, and easy to change.

9. Terraform Variable Types – Table
    string--------Stores text values-------------- ----"East US"---------------Location, resource names
    number-----------Stores numeric values-----------------3 ------------------VM count, port numbers
    list(string)------Ordered list of values---------["10.0.0.0/16"]-------CIDR blocks, subnets
    map(string) ------Key‑value pairs---------------{ dev = "B2s" }---------VM sizes per environment
    set(string)----------Unique unordered values----------["10.0.0.1"]---------NSG rules, allowed IPs
    Example : 
      #string Variable 
                variable "location" {
                  type    = string
                  default = "East US"
                }
    #map(string) Variable 
                    variable "vms" {
                      type = map(string)
                      default = {
                        vm1 = "Standard_B2s"
                        vm2 = "Standard_D2s_v3"
                      }
                    }
      # number Variable
                    variable "vm_count" {
                    type    = number
                    default = 3
                  }
      # bool Variable
                      variable "enable_public_ip" {
                    type    = bool
                    default = true
                  }
  #  list(string) Variable
                      variable "address_spaces" {
                        type    = list(string)
                        default = ["10.0.0.0/16"]
                      }
  
10 . What is diffrence between terraform import VS data block 
    terraform import: 
          terraform import is a CLI command used to add an already‑existing resource into Terraform state so Terraform can manage it.
          ✅ After import:
                            Resource is in terraform.tfstate
                            Terraform can update / destroy it
          ✅ When do you use terraform import?
                              Resource was created manually (Azure Portal, CLI), You now want Terraform to manage it.
----------
terraform import azurerm_linux_virtual_machine.vm \
/subscriptions/<sub-id>/resourceGroups/rg-demo/providers/Microsoft.Compute/virtualMachines/existing-v
---------
  What is a data block?
A data block is used to read information about existing resources.
          ✅ Terraform:
                              Reads values
                              Does NOT manage the resource
                              Cannot delete or modify it
11. What is a Module in Terraform?
        A Terraform module is a reusable, configurable block of infrastructure code that helps organize and standardize resource creation.

